# Walkthrough: Text-to-SQL Tool Implementation

I have successfully implemented the Text-to-SQL tool for your KLE Research AI Chatbot. The AI can now perform live database queries to answer complex questions about faculty, publications, and institutional metrics.

## Changes Made

### 1. Database Integration
- **Installed** `@supabase/supabase-js` to handle database communication.
- **Created** [supabaseClient.js](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/Downloads/RIA-Dashboard-L1-Interface%28ChatBot%29/ria-dashboard/src/supabaseClient.js) to initialize the connection to your local Supabase instance (`http://127.0.0.1:54321`).

### 2. SQL Tool & Metadata
- **Created** [sqlTool.js](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/Downloads/RIA-Dashboard-L1-Interface%28ChatBot%29/ria-dashboard/src/tools/sqlTool.js) which:
    - Defines the `execute_sql` tool for Groq.
    - Contains a condensed version of your database schema for the LLM's context.
    - Implements the execution logic (restricted to `SELECT` queries).

### 3. Chatbot Upgrade
- **Updated** [AIChatbot.jsx](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/Downloads/RIA-Dashboard-L1-Interface%28ChatBot%29/ria-dashboard/src/components/AIChatbot.jsx):
    - **Tool-calling Loop**: The chatbot now follows the assistant/tool/assistant loop required for complex multi-step reasoning.
    - **System Prompt**: Now includes the full schema and instructions on when to use the SQL tool.
    - **Bug Fixes**: Corrected regex escaping issues (`\\s` -> `\s`) that were previously breaking name and year searches.
    - **Memory**: Increased conversation history from 4 to 6 turns for better follow-up handling.

## 🚀 Required Action: Database Setup

To enable the AI to execute raw SQL, you **must** create a special helper function in your Supabase SQL Editor. Run the following query in your [Supabase Dashboard](http://127.0.0.1:54323) (or local SQL runner):

```sql
/**
 * Enables raw SQL execution for the Text-to-SQL tool.
 * SECURITY DEFINER ensures it runs with database owner permissions.
 */
CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION exec_sql(query_text TEXT)
RETURNS JSONB 
LANGUAGE plpgsql 
SECURITY DEFINER 
AS $$
DECLARE
    result JSONB;
BEGIN
    -- Execute the dynamic query and aggregate results into a JSON array
    EXECUTE 'SELECT json_agg(t) FROM (' || query_text || ') t' INTO result;
    RETURN result;
END;
$$;
```

## How to Test
1. Restart your dev server (`npm run dev`).
2. Open the chatbot and ask:
   - *"How many faculty members are in the CSE department?"*
   - *"List the titles of publications from 2024."*
   - *"Who are the top 3 faculty members by Scopus citations?"*
